1. In `IoTDBStatement.executeSQL`, there are many branches. I see that the last branch is equipped with StatusCode. Do the previous branches need that？
2. Does the client need to print the errorCode? As in the `AbstractClient.executeQuery`, when an exeception is caught, the current information printed is:
```
    } catch (Exception e) {
      println("Msg: " + e.getMessage());
      handleException(e);
    }
```

